result.execSummary:
The defendant Clifford Henry Wilson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Time served sentence with credit for 3 days of prior time served.
No DNA sample ordered as Defendant previously provided the same through another conviction.  Mandatory DNA Surcharge ordered.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 1:08 PM:  Defendant Clifford Henry Wilson in court with attorney Katena Roberts-Turner, both appearing via video.  Defendant Clifford Henry Wilson in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and potential punishment.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Per SPD:  If released, Defendant will no longer qualify due to earnings.  ADA had sent an offer on resolution to SPD.    Upon conferring with Defendant, SPD states he will accept the State's offer and resolve today.  Court entertains waiver of personal appearance.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of personal appearance.    Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea OAR 1: NC   Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Statement by Def prior to SEH:  None offered.  The Court:  Accepts resolution and imposes 3 days WCJ, time served SEH with credit for 3 days and Court Costs - 60 DTP or PP.  No  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights Faxed to WCJ.
